A very warm welcome and spiritually enhancing. Loved the Rabbi and the Cantor and how they touched the hearts of the congregation. The Jewish Reconstructionist stream has much to offer to many. Thank you.
DrBob

originalText.text:
A wonderful Jewish community! As new nyc residents, we began exploring the neighborhood and found West End Synagogue. It was at the very beginning of the COVID lockdown, and we began attending services virtually through Zoom. We were impressed from the beginning with the way we were recognized as newcomers and very warmly welcomed. We were treated as part of the community from the start.
Elevator construction is nearing completion, then we must wait for inspection. It will be a major improvement!

originalText.text: With the gradual fading of the Upper West side qualities, it is wonderful to find a community that holds those qualities dear. Intellectually stimulating, artistic, diverse ( yes even a synagogue can be) and intergenerational, West End Synagogue is an outpost of traditional Progressive thinking congregants who value the core concepts of  American Judaism. I joined for my kids but stayed for the deep friendships and community engagement.

originalText.text: Until my 60s, I never went into synagogues except for weddings, funerals, bar mitzvahs and the High Holidays.  Nothing about the services, the rhetoric, the participants attracted me, that is, until, at my wife's urging, I went to West End Synagogue.  In brief, the fierce intellectual independence of the members, encouraged by the clergy, united by a desire to know more about their past and their present, has become addictive.  It's not a place to stand pat, to ignore others, to abandon hope or curiosity.

originalText.text: Warm welcoming community. Amazing Rabbi. I adore this intimate synagogue occupies an old library, and remains a library for it's members. The shabbat lunch after services provided an opportunity to get to know people in a relaxed setting.
